{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot11EditorPathsC15isSelfContainedSbyF","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isSelfContained","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"title":"isSelfContained()"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if the editor is marked as self-contained, "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" otherwise. When self-contained mode is enabled, user configuration, data and cache files are saved in an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"editor_data\/"},{"text":" folder next to the editor binary. This makes portable usage easier and ensures the Godot editor minimizes file writes outside its own folder. Self-contained mode is not available for exported projects.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/editorpaths\/isselfcontained()"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorPaths"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isSelfContained","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-contained mode can be enabled by creating a file named "},{"code":"._sc_","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_sc_"},{"type":"text","